result.name: Veggie Spinner

reviews.text: It has some good affordable options like a wrap + soup or filling combo sets (soup, salad, juice, and main entree). Everything tasted fresh. I got a set for dinner but I can see myself going back to take away a wrap + soup or trying a different combo set.  I’m not fully vegetarian but like to explore a city’s veggie / vegan options. This place has great veggie + vegan choices with a western and asian cuisine / ingredient inspiration. The chef / owner is also really friendly and welcoming! Also make sure to bring cash.

Great food!
A small place but such good and fresh food. I go once a week at least even though I'm not vegetarian. The avocado linguine are really great, I can only recommend.
There is a lot of choice for every taste and very well presented as well.
I didn't feel it was expensive, but see for yourself.
Service can be somewhat slow when busy but I can also take away in less than 5 minutes. Be patient, good food doesn't always come fast! 😉
There is also daily fresh fruits and vegetables to buy of very good quality.
The owners might not seem very friendly to foreigners to start with, but it's all because of a language barrier. Once you know them, they are very nice 😀
Did I mention it's trying its best to be eco-friendly? No plastic straw, paper boxes and bags if you don't bring your own, etc.
I'm very happy to have discovered this place 👍
Small cozy eatery that serves vegetarian food of various styles. The Turkish wrap with tofu, asparagus, egg, spinach, eggplants tasted nice. Will probably come back for more when time allows.

Our only regret was not finding this little spot sooner! Unfortunately we came across Veggie Spinner on our last day in Hong Kong and as soon as I saw the menu I knew I would have a hard time choosing from so many amazing options! The food is fresh, tasty, nutritious, and made with a lot of care. Great service and lovely little space to dine!
I cannot recommend this place enough! An amazing option for healthy, delicious food. A great find for the neighborhood.
